tence foundation still maps to `endpoint-tool-management.md`, and re-ran the mandatory gates; `npm run db:prepare`, `npm run test:unit`, and `npm run verify` all passed.\\\\n - 2026-05-05T17:58:28+09:00 - Re-read the requested repository docs, inspected the current Prisma/SQLite schema, migrations, seed defaults, generated DB docs, and idempotency test, then re-ran the mandatory gates; `npm run db:prepare`, `npm run test:unit`, and `npm run verify` all passed with no scope changes needed.\\\\n+- 2026-05-05T18:03:10+09:00 - Revalidated the existing endpoint persistence foundation against the current task prompt; Prisma/SQLite schema, migrations, idempotent seed defaults, generated DB docs, and repeatability coverage are present, and `npm run db:prepare`, `npm run test:unit`, and `npm run verify` all passed.\\\\ndiff --git a/state/last-result.txt b/state/last-result.txt\\\\nindex 0ee0344..5f8244f 100644\\\\n--- a/state/last-result.txt\\\\n+++ b/state/last-result.txt\\\\n@@ -1,10 +1,12 @@\\\\n Completed `endpoint-domain-and-schema`.\\\\n \\\\n-I re-read the required docs, inspected the existing Prisma/SQLite persistence foundation, updated the task progress log, and wrote the operator handoff to [state/last-result.txt](/Users/stevenna/WebstormProjects/mina-mock-mcpserver/state/last-result.txt). No product-code changes were needed.\\\\n+What changed: Re-read the required task docs, inspected the existing Prisma/SQLite endpoint persistence foundation, appended this run's progress note to `docs/exec-plans/active/001-endpoint-domain-and-schema.md`, and refreshed this operator handoff. No product-code changes were needed.\\\\n+\\\\n+Exit criteria: Appear satisfied. The repository has Prisma/SQLite migrations and schema for endpoints, ordered parameters, response cases, timestamps, delete-code/default/failure fields, immutable endpoint IDs, idempotent seed defaults, generated DB schema docs, and repeatability coverage.\\\\n \\\\n Checks passed:\\\\n - `npm run db:prepare`\\\